### Question 1 `[KTU University Exam — Jun 2024, Module 1, 3 marks]`

**Q: Differentiate between unit testing and mutation testing. List any two mutation operators with examples.**

**Model Answer (≈ 3-mark depth):**

| Aspect | Unit Testing | Mutation Testing |
|---|---|---|
| **Goal** | Verify correctness of individual units | Assess *strength* of the test suite |
| **Input** | Program + test cases | Program + existing test suite |
| **Technique** | Execute tests on original code | Execute same tests on *mutated* code |
| **Output metric** | Pass / fail + coverage % | Mutation Score % |
| **Tools** | JUnit, TestNG, NUnit | PIT, MuJava, Major |

**Two mutation operators (with examples):**

- **ROR (Relational Operator Replacement):** `if (x > 0)` becomes `if (x >= 0)`.
- **AOR (Arithmetic Operator Replacement):** `a = b + c` becomes `a = b - c`.

**Marking scheme expected:** 1 mark for the comparison table (any 3 valid points), 1 mark each for the two mutation operators with example. Total 3 marks.

